column1:
Insult refers to language that explicitly attacks the author of the hateful comment, including 
(a) vulgar insults “your a**hole”; 
(b) intelligence insults “so stupid I can’t help you”;
(c) dehumanization “you are just trash”; or 
(d) threatening language "beat me if you dare”.

Denigrating, insolvent or contemptuous statements

A message is considered aggressive if it (implicitly or explicitly) presents, incites, threatens, suggests or alludes to:
1. attitudes, violent actions,  hostility or commission of offenses against women;
2. justify or legitimize an aggressive action against women.
